# .env.example — copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored; never commit real values.
# The agent reads these from the process environment (os.environ); .env is just a convenient
# way to populate it locally. The agent is LOCAL-ONLY: it runs on a workstation, produces
# Dockerfile.agent, and hands that to CI. CI stays keyless (GitHub OIDC) and must NOT receive
# the Kilo key — the pipeline never calls the LLM, so do not wire KILO_API_KEY into CI.
KILO_API_KEY=
KILO_BASE_URL=https://api.kilo.ai/api/gateway
